Read and follow these cooking directions. Microwave Oven: Cook only one product at a time. 1. Open carton; do not remove fruit pie. Silver liner must be over top of fruit pie. 2. Microwave on High. 1100 watt oven or more: 5-1/2 to 6 minutes. Do not cook in microwave ovens below 1100 watts as fruit pie may not cook thoroughly. Conventional oven preparation is recommended. 3. Wrap crust edge with strip of aluminum foil. 2. Bake on cookie sheet for 43 to 45 minutes. Carefully remove as product will be hot. 3. Let stand 5 minutes. Check that fruit pie is cooked thoroughly. Internal temperature needs to reach 165 degrees F as measured by a food thermometer in several spots. Crust is golden brown and steam rises from filling. 4. Caution: Filling will be extremely hot.
